article.headline: East Tennessee State 90, Virginias-Wise 43
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Eryk Thomas and Dante Williams scored 14 points each to lead a balanced scoring attack as East Tennessee State beat Virginia-Wise 90-43 Friday night. ETSU (1-0) led 41-18 at halftime after scoring 19 straight points to break a 12-12 tie and go ahead 31-12. Courtney Pigram added 13 points and Mike Smith scored 11 as 11 Buccaneers scored. Virginia-Wise (0-1), which shot just 27.5 percent, was led by Zydrunas Rackauskas, Joey Blackwell and Jarred Soles with 9 points each. ETSU's biggest lead was 51 points, 89-38 with 1:43 left.
